ğŸŒŸ Introduction
The Screen Time Tracker Extension helps you monitor and track the amount of time you spend on each tab in your browser. This can help you manage your time better and increase productivity.

âœ¨ Features
Tracks screen time for each tab
User-friendly interface
Detailed reports of screen time
Lightweight and efficient
ğŸ› ï¸ Installation
Clone the repository:
```
git clone https://github.com/notcodesid/Screen-Time-Tracker-Extension.git
```
Navigate to the project directory:
```
cd Screen-Time-Tracker-Extension
```
Install dependencies:
```
npm install
```
Build the extension:
```
npm run build
```
Load the extension in your browser:

Open your browser's extensions page (usually chrome://extensions/ for Chrome).


Enable "Developer mode".

Click on "Load unpacked" and select the dist directory.


ğŸ“– Usage

Open your browser and click on the Screen Time Tracker Extension icon.

The extension will start tracking the time you spend on each tab.

You can view detailed reports and insights by clicking on the extension icon.

